items.sentence: Tom told me that he thought that Mary still lived in Australia.
I laughed when Tom told me that he was planning to get married.
Tom told me that he planned on waiting until Monday to do that.
Tom told me that he thought he was going to be able to do that.
Tom told me that he'd wait for us in front of the Hilton Hotel.
I don't think Tom is going to want to go to Australia with you.
I suspect that Tom won't tell Mary the real reason he did that.
I suspect that Tom is likely to do that when he's in Australia.
I suspect that Tom and Mary were planning to do that yesterday.
I suspect that Tom and Mary were able to do that by themselves.
